jade.story.prob
Class MixtureCategorical<K,V>

java.lang.Object
  jade.story.prob.MixtureCategorical<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - the type of the keys to the individual categorical distributions in the mixture
V - the type of the support of the categorical distributions in the mixture
public class MixtureCategorical<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object

Represents a mixture of categorical distributions over <V>. A mixture of distributions is a distribution which can be interpreted as being derived from an underlying set of distributions. In this case, each of these distributions is a Categorical. Each of the underlying distributions has a key so that conditional probabilities are easily calculator. The respective weights of each of the underlying distributions is represented as the ratio of the counts of the particular Categorical with respect to the sum of all the Categorical frequency sums.

support

public java.util.Set<V> support()
Returns the support of the distribution, which is the smallest set whose compliment has a cumulative probability of zero. In other words, it is the set of all values for which there is a non-zero count.

Returns:
the support of the mixture of categorical distribution
